cdu — charm disk usage
======================

cdu is a fork of gdu (https://github.com/dundee/gdu) by Daniel Milde,
distributed under the MIT License. The original copyright notice and license
text are preserved in LICENSE.md and continue to apply to all code inherited
from gdu — which is the entire disk-analysis engine: pkg/, report/, stdout/,
tui/ and internal/common/.

cdu is NOT the official gdu, is not affiliated with or endorsed by the gdu
project, and should not be reported to gdu's maintainers for bugs in its own
user interface. Report cdu issues at https://github.com/pottom/cdu/issues.

What cdu changes
----------------

cdu replaces gdu's interactive tview interface with a new one built on the
Charm stack, and adds theming, an installer and a self-updater. The scanning
engine is used as-is, not reimplemented. gdu's original interface remains
available via `cdu --classic`, and the non-interactive and JSON export modes
are byte-for-byte identical to gdu's.

